e\n*1395: [[John Moigne|Sir John Moigne]] (or Moyne) of Owermoigne\n*1396: Thomas Bonham\n*1397\u20131399: [[Richard Mawarden]] of Stratford sub Castle\n*1400: John Dauntsey\n{{colend}}\n\n===15th century===\n{{colbegin}}\n*1401: [[William Worfton]] of Broad Hinton and John Gawayne\n*1402: [[William Cheyne (died 1420)|William Cheyne]] of Brooke\n*1403\u20131404: [[Walter Beauchamp]]\n*1405: [[Walter Hungerford, 1st Baron Hungerford|Walter Hungerford]]\n*1406: Rad. (i.e. Radulphus for Rafe or Ralph) Grene (otherwise Green)\n*1407: [[Walter Beauchamp]]\n*1408: [[Robert Corbet (died 1417)|Sir Robert Corbet]]\n*1409: William Cheyne\n*1410: [[John Berkeley (died 1428)|Sir John Berkeley]] of [[Beverston Castle]]\n*1411: Thomas Bonham\n*1413: Sir Elias Delamere, Kt, of [[Fisherton Delamere]]\n*1414: [[Henry Thorpe]] of [[Newton Tony]]\n*1415: Thomas Calstone (otherwise Calston) of [[Littlecote House|Littlecote]] and [[Upton Lovell]]\n*1416: Robert Andrewe (or Andrew)\n*1417: William Finderne\n*1418: [[William Esturmy|Sir William Sturmy]], of [[Wulfhall]]\n*1419: Thomas Ringwood, of Loveraz Coulesfield\n*1420\u20131421: William Darell, of Littlecote\n*1422: William Darell, of Littlecote (see 1420)\n*1423: Sir Robert Shotesbrook (or Shottesbrook), Kt\n*1424: William Finderne\n*1425: Walter Pauncefoot\n*1426: [[John Stourton, 1st Baron Stourton|John Stourton]], of Stourton\n*1427: William Darell, of Littlecote (see 1420)\n*1428: John Pawlet, of Fisherton Delamere\n*1429: Sir John Bayntun, Kt, of Fallersdon\n*1430: David Cervington, of [[Longford Castle]]\n*1431: [[John Seymour (died 1464)|Sir John Seymour]], of [[Wulfhall]]\n*1432: Walter Strickland\n*1433: [[John Stourton, 1st Baron Stourton|Sir John Stourton]], of Stourton (see 1426)\n*1434: [[Stephen Popham (English MP)|Sir Stephen Popham]] of Popham\n*1435: Edmund or Edward Hungerford\n*1436: William Beauchamp\n*1437: [[John Stourton, 1st Baron Stourton|Sir John Stourton]] (see 1426)\n*1438: Sir John Lisle, Kt\n*1439: Joh